    • Constructor Detail

      • WebProxySettings

        public WebProxySettings(String hostName,
                        int port,
                        List<Pattern> noProxyHostPatterns,
                        String proxyUser,
                        hudson.util.Secret proxySecret)
        Convenience constructor, mostly for tests.
        Parameters:
        hostName - the name (or address) of the proxy server. May be null, meaning there is no proxy server configured.
        port - the port that the proxy server is listening on
        noProxyHostPatterns - a list of Pattern representing hosts that should not be proxied. May be null, meaning all hosts will be proxied.
        proxyUser - the name of the user with which to authenticate to the proxy server. May be null, meaning the proxy server doesn't need authentication.
        proxySecret - the password of the user with which to authenticate to the proxy server. May be null, meaning the proxy server doesn't need authentication.

      • WebProxySettings

        public WebProxySettings(hudson.ProxyConfiguration proxyConfiguration)
        Initialize a WebProxySettings from a Jenkins ProxyConfiguration.
        Parameters:
        proxyConfiguration - the proxy settings as obtained from Jenkins. May be null, meaning there is no proxy configured.

    • Method Detail

      • toProxyHost

        public ProxyHostEx toProxyHost(String hostToProxy)
        Initialize a ProxyHostEx from this WebProxySettings for the provided hostToProxy. May return null, which either means there is no proxy server configured or it does not apply to the provided hostToProxy.
        Parameters:
        hostToProxy - the name of the host for which proxying is considered.
        Returns:
        an instance of ProxyHostEx or null if no proxy is to be used.
